","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Worcester or York England":"York, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Chaddesley Corbett, Worcestershire, England":"Chaddesley Corbett, Worcestershire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wakeman","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: occupational name from Middle English <i>wakeman</i> ‘watchman, town guard’, also ‘municipal officer responsible for night-time security and the town musicians’. <i>Wakeman</i> was the title of the chief magistrate of the borough of Ripon until 1604, when it was changed to mayor. He was the head of the body of wakemen whose duty was to blow a cow's horn every night at nine o'clock. If between then and sunrise any burglary took place, it was made good at the public charge. See also   Watchman  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Watchman","meanings":["Native American (Navajo): from English <i>watchman</i>, probably used as a translation of a Navajo term for this occupation, <i>ha'asídí</i>.","English and Scottish: occupational name from Middle English <i>waccheman</i> ‘watchman, guard, sentry’, also used as a nickname for a person characterised by wakefulness. Compare   Wakeman  ."]},{"name":"Watchorn","meanings":["English (East Midlands, especially Leicestershire): nickname apparently from Middle English <i>wache</i> ‘vigil, wake, watch’ (Old English <i>wacce</i>) + <i>horn</i> ‘horn’. Compare the discussion of   Wakeman  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Wakeman was born in 1275, in York, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Walter Wakeman, was 20 and his mother, Elizabeth Coply, was 25. He married Elizabeth Grene in 1295, in Worcestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son.